{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"13d2235c-5bf0-428b-ac44-0463977d48aa","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"13f204bf-df64-4450-b143-45ec8c302c82","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":302,"requestId":"3409:1E3288:A1EE11:BE5E75:69F3FF13"},"id":"4bee0262-5cf4-409c-9cf2-7978a6f9c59a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:17:14.244Z","parentId":"9a806e53-bed4-4d3f-8b86-af7fd6689ae5"}
